caption: Highly recommend their combo number 13. Perfect fried pork chop. Fast, juicy, crispy, not too dry or greasy. Rice and beans are also tasty. I ate this many years ago it still the same, perfect.  That’s how their Philly cheesesteak likes. Not like Philly cheesesteaks in Philly but still not bad.  Tonight one of the plantains is not well done, kind of hard. Beans are not soft enough. But it’s alright.  A lot of options. Clean, tasty, affordable, exquisitely. Order normally take 15-20 minutes to prepare. Suggest you order take out through the phone or dine in. You can order by English or Spanish.

I venture to this little spot probably at least a couple times a month, it's one of the first places I take friends to get a bite to eat in Brooklyn since it's only a few blocks from where I live. It's clean, staff is friendly, and food is pretty decent for the price and cooked fast! If your nearby definitely give the place a go and try their chicken parmesan sandwich, it's the only thing I get. Don't expect anything fancy though, it's a pretty bare bones type of restaurant but that's all you need!
